1
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:18,940
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:23,912
<i>[Episode 28]</i>

3
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:29,540
The things we usually can't find pop up once we start packing.

4
00:01:29,540 --> 00:01:32,150
Exactly. I can't find them when I want to use them.

5
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:34,841
Look! A dozen nail clippers.

6
00:01:34,841 --> 00:01:37,680
We even have these old mobile phones. Look.

7
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:39,020
We can't throw these away.

8
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:42,280
But... what's the use of them? They're so old.

9
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:45,590
- We can keep them as a memory. These things...
- Mom!

10
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:47,766
Come over here.

11
00:01:47,766 --> 00:01:50,920
- Take a look at this.
- Throw away whatever seems useless. There's no need to ask me.

12
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:54,810
Hold on. What are you throwing away? Let me check.

13
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,744
It's so dusty.

14
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:02,810
Grandma bought this fan for me when I was in elementary school, right?

15
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:06,270
Why do we still have this? It's been over 20 years. I'm sure it's broken.

16
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:08,842
Dou, you should really throw this away.

17
00:02:08,842 --> 00:02:11,406
Why are you wiping it?

18
00:02:11,406 --> 00:02:13,180
I'll check if it can still work.

19
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:16,246
Don't try it. I bet it's broken.

20
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:19,410
Look.

21
00:02:21,810 --> 00:02:24,020
Look. The quality of older products is much better.

22
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:26,100
It can still work.

23
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:31,090
Her grandma reared over 30 chickens just to buy her this.

24
00:02:31,090 --> 00:02:34,918
She sold their eggs and saved over ¥100 for this.

25
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,060
<i>Is it cooling?</i>

26
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:58,880
All right. It's too old for our new house.

27
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,310
Let's not keep it.

28
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:01,894
I'll keep it.

29
00:03:01,894 --> 00:03:03,850
It's Grandma's wind.

30
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,630
Grandma's wind?

31
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:08,838
Your grandma would be exasperated if she knew about this.

32
00:03:08,838 --> 00:03:11,150
This is Secretary Li of Yunmiao Village.

33
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:12,800
This is the village director.

34
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,430
This is Vice President Wang of our group.

35
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,310
- Vice President Wang.
- Nice to meet you.

36
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:17,660
Welcome.

37
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:19,260
- Nice to meet you, Vice President Wang.
- Nice to meet you.

38
00:03:19,260 --> 00:03:22,330
This is Deputy Director Xu of our group.

39
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:23,990
- Hello, Deputy Director Xu.
- Deputy Director Xu.

40
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:26,910
- A'Yao.
- Brother Liu, it's been a long time.

41
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:28,590
It's been a long time.

42
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:30,470
Chairman Xie, we meet again.

43
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:32,380
Why don't I see Hongdou?

44
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:34,570
She's not here.

45
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,250
Where is she?

46
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:40,400
Look at him. He only remembers beautiful women.

47
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:43,180
A'Yao, let me formally introduce him to you.

48
00:03:43,180 --> 00:03:49,432
In fact, Xiao Zhang is our chief designer and one of our partners.

49
00:03:49,432 --> 00:03:51,180
Chief designer and partner?

50
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:52,260
You're so young!

51
00:03:52,260 --> 00:03:54,431
Last time, I joined Brother Liu and his wife on their trip.

52
00:03:54,431 --> 00:03:56,950
I was afraid of bothering you, so I said I was their assistant.

53
00:03:56,950 --> 00:03:59,080
So sweet. It's no trouble at all.

54
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,750
A'Yao, I've already introduced Chief Designer Zhang to you.

55
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:04,930
I'll introduce the entire team to you later.

56
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:06,120
Great!

57
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:09,910
Today, the village has made arrangements. I'm just helping out. All right?

58
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:11,460
Xinxin.

59
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:12,430
Come on, Secretary Li.

60
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:14,930
Let me do the introductions. President Liu.

61
00:04:21,140 --> 00:04:23,700
<i>[Xie Zhiyao: Real-time update. They're here.]</i>

62
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:26,640
♫ <i>Stars in the sky</i> ♫

63
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:29,320
♫ <i>Picking mushrooms</i> ♫

64
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:32,300
♫ <i>Mushrooms fill the basket</i> ♫

65
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:35,160
♫ <i>A pen in my hand</i> ♫

66
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,860
<i>[Do your best. Good luck.]</i>
♫ <i>The pen is leaking</i> ♫

67
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:40,800
♫ <i>What can I do?</i> ♫

68
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:44,340
♫ <i>Taking mung beans</i> ♫

69
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,000
♫ <i>Mung beans are delicious</i> ♫

70
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,760
♫ <i>Gingers are fresh</i> ♫

71
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,720
♫ <i>Fresh gingers are spicy</i> ♫

72
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,430
We'll be right over for a meal.

73
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:01,286
You can start cooking now.

74
00:05:01,286 --> 00:05:04,076
Especially your sour papaya fish and braised chicken.

75
00:05:04,076 --> 00:05:07,220
Okay. Thank you, Aunty Hua.

76
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:10,190
Chairman Xie, I heard Xiao Zhang mention discussions when they head back.

77
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:11,970
Is that some kind of tactic?

78
00:05:11,970 --> 00:05:14,120
Nah. It's just a meeting.

79
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:17,340
Relax. I think success is in our hands this time.

80
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:20,310
♫ <i>Slim and elegant</i> ♫

81
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:25,550
♫ <i>My baby, time to sleep</i> ♫

82
00:05:25,550 --> 00:05:27,640
Sister Qiu. Yes.

83
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:31,190
When I was in Yunnan, that's the village I stayed in.

84
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:34,289
A homestay has been built there.

85
00:05:34,289 --> 00:05:36,950
The village is also in development.

86
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:41,314
If the owner hadn't fallen ill, it wouldn't have been sold.

87
00:05:41,314 --> 00:05:44,800
I think your homestays are doing quite well,

88
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,260
I was wondering if you'd consider expanding branches.

89
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:50,290
<i>Hongdou, why don't you buy it?</i>

90
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:53,230
<i>Working at a hotel is exhausting anyway.</i>

91
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:55,590
<i>It's better to be your own boss.</i>

92
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:57,960
I really hadn't considered this.

93
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:00,040
<i>Didn't you quit your job?</i>

94
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,960
<i>Is there a better job offer?</i>

95
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:06,144
A friend invited me to join their Staff Training Department.

96
00:06:06,144 --> 00:06:08,783
<i>Is the salary lower than your reception post?</i>

97
00:06:08,783 --> 00:06:12,111
Yes. The benefit is the regular working hours.

98
00:06:12,111 --> 00:06:14,210
I'm not really thinking about starting a business.

99
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:18,078
After all, starting one requires quite a sum of money. Right?

100
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:20,650
<i>You're not wrong in thinking so.</i>

101
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:23,170
<i>It's secure to work as an employee for a stable salary.</i>

102
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:25,430
<i>Starting a business is indeed risky.</i>

103
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:48,460
<i>[Dou: Asleep?]</i>

104
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:50,460
<i>[Nope.]</i>

105
00:06:55,460 --> 00:06:58,160
<i>[Alone in your room?]</i>

106
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,560
<i>[Yeah.]</i>

107
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,500
Hello.

108
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,430
Are you still awake? Aren't you tired?

109
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,210
<i>I'm tired.</i>

110
00:07:11,210 --> 00:07:12,870
I've been busy all day.

111
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:15,130
My legs are restless, so I can't sleep.

112
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,620
<i>What are you doing?</i>

113
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:18,620
Packing.

114
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:21,370
Don't harp on this.

115
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:22,830
You've done all you could do.

116
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:25,880
Regardless of the result, you've put in the effort.

117
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,340
Mr. Ma's recent sign-off on Moments.

118
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:33,480
Do good deeds, and don't ask about the future.

119
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:40,060
♫ <i>I'm searching for a meadow of mine</i> ♫

120
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:48,420
♫ Till you came in with the breeze ♫

121
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:55,200
Listen.

122
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:00,330
What is it?

123
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:03,810
The wind has risen. A really strong wind.

124
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:07,310
♫ <i>A feeling rushes over me</i> ♫

125
00:08:07,310 --> 00:08:11,749
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

126
00:08:11,749 --> 00:08:15,054
I think I can hear it.

127
00:08:15,054 --> 00:08:17,160
How's the weather over there?

128
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,830
It's pretty good.

129
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:22,530
It's raining.

130
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:25,520
<i>Dou, it's raining! There are quilts drying on the rooftop.</i>

131
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,960
<i>Come with me to collect them.</i>

132
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:29,652
Okay, Mom. Right away.

133
00:08:29,652 --> 00:08:31,940
Was your mom talking to you?

134
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:35,230
<i>Who are you chatting with on the phone?</i>

135
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:38,040
- Someone. I'm coming.
<i>- Hurry up.</i>

136
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:40,820
I need to hang up. I'll call you later.

137
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:47,690
♫ <i>We close our eyes to feel</i> ♫

138
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:50,590
♫ <i>And smile</i> ♫

139
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:03,616
♪ <i>Even if fall into the horizon</i> ♪

140
00:09:03,616 --> 00:09:06,870
♪ <i>I want to bloom in the land</i> ♪

141
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:09,900
♪ <i>Even the finest dust</i> ♪

142
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:14,084
♪ <i>Can gain your favor</i> ♪

143
00:09:14,084 --> 00:09:17,026
You sing so well!

144
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:22,570
♪ Just like a match! ♪

145
00:09:22,570 --> 00:09:26,170
♪ It can ignite a sea of fire! ♪

146
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,720
Sister, calm down. I'm driving.

147
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:30,080
♪ Chase the future! ♪

148
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,420
♪ Never return! ♪

149
00:09:31,420 --> 00:09:33,970
Sister, you can be excited, but we have to be safe.

150
00:09:33,970 --> 00:09:37,340
♪ Waiting to fly to the stage! ♪

151
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:41,260
♪ Let light prove my existence! ♪

152
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:44,410
♪ Even the finest dust! ♪

153
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:45,740
♪ Can gain you favor! ♪

154
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:47,980
Sister, don't tickle me.

155
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:56,210
Sister!

156
00:09:56,650 --> 00:09:58,150
Sister!

157
00:10:00,620 --> 00:10:01,860
Are you okay?

158
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:03,660
Are you hurt?

159
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,630
What's wrong?

160
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,200
Did you hit your head?

161
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:15,911
- Are you all right?
- ♪ Even if I fall into the horizon! ♪

162
00:10:15,911 --> 00:10:18,140
- ♪ I want to... ♪
- Still singing?

163
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:20,440
♪ Bloom in the land! ♪

164
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:24,276
♪ If the fire inside hasn't been extinguished! ♪

165
00:10:24,276 --> 00:10:28,585
♪ It's not a failure to be beaten and bruised! ♪

166
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:32,930
♪ If dreaming is a sin! ♪

167
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:37,100
♪ I'll spend my life with it! ♪

168
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,080
♪ No regrets! ♪

169
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:43,180
- No regrets!
- ♪ No regrets... ♪

170
00:10:44,830 --> 00:10:49,410
♪ Waiting to fly to the stage! ♪

171
00:10:49,410 --> 00:10:54,086
♪ Let light prove my existence! ♪

172
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:58,090
♪ Even the finest dust! ♪

173
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:02,201
<i>Mr. Hu was on the scooter with Sister Manjun.</i>

174
00:11:02,201 --> 00:11:03,648
<i>They accidentally fell into the field.</i>

175
00:11:03,648 --> 00:11:06,986
<i>Does she like Mr. Hu?</i>

176
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:10,970
No way. Sister Manjun's daughter is already in college.

177
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:13,930
She has such a grown daughter?

178
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:16,198
She doesn't look like she does!

179
00:11:16,198 --> 00:11:18,930
Sister Manjun said that she didn't want to hinder her child's college entrance examinations,

180
00:11:18,930 --> 00:11:22,626
so she filed for divorce only after that.

181
00:11:22,626 --> 00:11:26,290
<i>But does her daughter being in college</i>

182
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:28,722
affect her potential feelings for Mr. Hu?

183
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,980
Nope.

184
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:35,236
At first glance, Mr. Hu is poor, ugly, and sleazy.

185
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:37,240
<i>Sister Manjun is rich, beautiful, and elegant.</i>

186
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,120
<i>No one would think of them as a couple.</i>

187
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:43,266
It's unlike how Hongdou and Chairman Xie seem so compatible.

188
00:11:43,266 --> 00:11:45,220
We're compatible?

189
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:46,570
Get married!

190
00:11:46,570 --> 00:11:48,030
<i>Stop that.</i>

191
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,838
It's a bad ending for them.

192
00:11:51,690 --> 00:11:54,402
I don't like this ending.

193
00:11:55,770 --> 00:11:58,770
If readers ask you to change the ending,

194
00:11:58,770 --> 00:12:00,940
will you do it?

195
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:02,780
<i>She won't.</i>

196
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,200
Will you?

197
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:09,500
<i>Dou, the moving truck is here. Come on.</i>

198
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,610
<i>- Let's go.</i>
- Okay.

199
00:12:11,610 --> 00:12:13,530
The moving truck is here. I have to go.

200
00:12:13,530 --> 00:12:14,750
- I'm hanging up.
- Bye-bye.

201
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:15,920
Good luck with the move.

202
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:18,221
Okay, bye-bye. Good luck with the move.

203
00:12:18,221 --> 00:12:19,640
Bye-bye.

204
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:27,270
3.52 meters.

205
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:32,650
- 3.77 meters.
- 3.42.

206
00:12:32,650 --> 00:12:36,690
Why did you waste such a huge space in the original design for a yard?

207
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,370
Is it a waste?

208
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:40,360
I don't think so.

209
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:43,502
We can add a layer here.

210
00:12:43,502 --> 00:12:45,870
- No, you can't.
- We can't?

211
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,740
There's a height restriction.

212
00:12:47,740 --> 00:12:49,491
The facade of the buildings can't be changed either.

213
00:12:49,491 --> 00:12:51,120
It has to be consistent with the residential homes.

214
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,690
Brother Ji, take a look at this place.

215
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:56,470
Can it be altered for a coffee bar so parties can be held?

216
00:12:56,470 --> 00:12:58,300
There can't be parties at night.

217
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,610
This place has to be kept quiet after 8:30 p.m.

218
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:02,870
The residents need to have their rest.

219
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:09,190
This place is backward and has too many restrictions.

220
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:10,240
Why are there so many rules?

221
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:13,290
I bet the broken capital chain of the original owner is just an excuse.

222
00:13:13,290 --> 00:13:16,170
He probably wants a takeover due to the unfavorable situation.

223
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:19,500
Exactly. The countryside is what it is.

224
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:22,138
We can't take over this land.

225
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:48,888
Which spoiled brat is this?

226
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,800
Brother?

227
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,640
Why are you throwing stones at the glass?

228
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:01,640
- For fun.
- For fun?

229
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:04,700
I'll... go home to cook.

230
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:20,440
Which one is better? Help me choose one.

231
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:23,110
All of them are fine.

232
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,340
You're at it again.

233
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:31,260
Can't live without your phone, right?

234
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:33,812
Is shopping with me that boring?

235
00:15:33,812 --> 00:15:36,174
I'm just browsing.

236
00:15:36,690 --> 00:15:37,740
Fine.

237
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,810
Anyway, we've moved homes.

238
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:42,390
If you need to hurry back to Beijing, get going.

239
00:15:42,390 --> 00:15:45,123
I'm sick of seeing you around.

240
00:15:45,123 --> 00:15:48,528
I promised Kexin to be the first relative her baby meets.

241
00:15:48,528 --> 00:15:51,720
Isn't she due next month?

242
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,870
That's still a long time.

243
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:58,290
Isn't it nice to have me around?

244
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:04,399
Be frank with me. Are you discontent with your current job?

245
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,910
It's... okay.

246
00:16:06,910 --> 00:16:09,986
I work from 9 to 5, and the pay is decent.

247
00:16:09,986 --> 00:16:12,390
I think you're getting lazy.

248
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:14,522
It's so hard to find a job now.

249
00:16:14,522 --> 00:16:16,290
You have to be more eager.

250
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:19,283
If I were a boss, I wouldn't hire you.

251
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:21,650
We barely see each other.

252
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:24,658
Now that I'm back for a few days, you're tired of me.

253
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,520
People shouldn't stay idle all the time.

254
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:31,690
Dad said the same thing.

255
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:33,410
Him? He should ditch this notion.

256
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:35,450
With his lumbar disc, what can he even do?

257
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:38,710
Does he intend to work until he's bedridden forever?

258
00:16:38,710 --> 00:16:41,050
Why is he running that small supermarket and playing boss?

259
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:43,290
He's daydreaming.

260
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,450
Be careful.

261
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,760
Why did you buy so much toilet paper?

262
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,690
People will think we have tons of butts at home waiting to be wiped.

263
00:16:57,690 --> 00:17:01,490
Where's you mom? She went to Building 8 to see the neighbor's renovations.

264
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:03,726
What neighbor?

265
00:17:03,726 --> 00:17:06,170
My high school classmate who also bought a home here.

266
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:07,450
Which classmate?

267
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:08,970
Li Yulin.

268
00:17:08,970 --> 00:17:10,960
We used to be right after each other's desks in the classroom.

269
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,450
You never mentioned this before.

270
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:13,960
I thought she was a nuisance.

271
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,100
By the way, you have a delivery from Yunnan.

272
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,300
The sender's surname is Xie.

273
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:19,900
Xie Zhiyao?

274
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,110
Who is he?

275
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:23,010
A village beau in Yunnan.

276
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:32,834
What is this?

277
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:38,020
- Plums.
- That's a lot of plums. Two boxes of them.

278
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:40,950
When... When will we even finish everything?

279
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:47,280
"Peaches for plums, favor for favor."

280
00:17:48,210 --> 00:17:49,550
He sure is mindful.

281
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:51,340
What's this about returning favors with plums?

282
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,860
Puns are in fashion now.

283
00:17:52,860 --> 00:17:55,070
All right. Let's move this to the kitchen.

284
00:17:55,070 --> 00:17:56,270
Come on.

285
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:04,620
Here you go. I'll get you guys some water.

286
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:11,570
Thank you.

287
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:13,910
Make room for me.

288
00:18:13,910 --> 00:18:14,920
You're here.

289
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,420
Sister.

290
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:20,240
By the way, Brother, this is for mouth ulcers.

291
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,520
Apply this and you'll be fine.

292
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:22,510
Great.

293
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:23,780
You're sweet.

294
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:27,060
I'm not the horse ranch belle without a reason.

295
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:29,090
Okay, let's start our meeting.

296
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:33,670
Look at the third quarter development plan of the horse ranch.

297
00:18:33,670 --> 00:18:35,550
There are three main aspects.

298
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:00,540
All right. That's all for today's meeting.

299
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,350
- You can head back to work.
- Okay.

300
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:03,830
Manager Chun, is there anything else?

301
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:05,740
Nope. You can leave first.

302
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:06,650
We'll be off.

303
00:19:06,650 --> 00:19:08,570
Go on. Don't wait for me.

304
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,770
Brother, we're leaving.

305
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:12,800
We're off.

306
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:15,210
- Take care.
- Bye-bye.

307
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:20,530
What's up? What else is there?

308
00:19:22,580 --> 00:19:26,580
Brother, have you been really stressed lately?

309
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,428
I'm fine.

310
00:19:30,428 --> 00:19:33,004
Your face is so overcast.

311
00:19:33,004 --> 00:19:36,962
Is there an issue with the bookstore?

312
00:19:36,962 --> 00:19:39,270
Not really.

313
00:19:39,270 --> 00:19:43,619
I just... thought things were going smoothly,

314
00:19:43,619 --> 00:19:45,760
but there's been radio silence lately.

315
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:48,430
Everything has been left hanging, so I'm worried.

316
00:19:48,430 --> 00:19:52,994
We haven't resold the homestay either.

317
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:57,256
To be frank,

318
00:19:57,256 --> 00:20:00,150
this matter has nothing to do with us. You're just helping them.

319
00:20:00,150 --> 00:20:02,432
Just do what you can.

320
00:20:02,432 --> 00:20:07,900
Xiaochun, you have to expand and broaden your vision.

321
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,640
This problem can't be solved just by broadening my vision.

322
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,110
I just don't want you to be anxious.

323
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,670
Got it.

324
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:15,564
Get going.

325
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:18,370
I'm leaving.

326
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,220
Brother,

327
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:35,623
did you read Xu Hongdou's WeChat Moments?

328
00:20:35,623 --> 00:20:37,420
What's wrong?

329
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:45,350
<i>[Thanks to a certain someone for the plums, though they're very sour.]</i>

330
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,330
Is there anything else?

331
00:20:57,330 --> 00:20:58,840
Nope.

332
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,891
Well, get going. Xiao Hu Lu is waiting for you.

333
00:21:01,891 --> 00:21:04,930
Okay. I'm leaving.

334
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:07,290
I'm really leaving.

335
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:11,370
Bye-bye.

336
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,800
<i>[The plums were just picked, so they're sour. They won't go bad easily. Eat them after some time.]</i>

337
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:36,800
<i>[You sent too much. My dad said you beat up the plum seller.]</i>

338
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:46,300
<i>[I traveled so far for them. Of course, I have to pick more.]</i>

339
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,100
<i>[Thanks for the hard work.]</i>

340
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,500
<i>[Thank you~]</i>

341
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,544
<i>[Hahaha]</i>

342
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,400
Feels amazing.

343
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:34,400
Look! You have knots here and here.

344
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,700
That's why your back always hurts.

345
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:38,800
They have to be unknotted.

346
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:44,000
We also have villagers skilled in massage, you know?

347
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:46,500
Their technique pales in comparison to yours.

348
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:49,400
Why are you so talented?

349
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:51,600
My ex-husband's cervical spine used to hurt,

350
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:53,800
so I went to learn from a masseur.

351
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:57,200
You're impressive! Amazing!

352
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,700
Bear with this for a little longer.

353
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:01,900
Okay.

354
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,400
I'm back.

355
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,700
Xiao Huang, you're back.

356
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:06,800
You're back.

357
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,000
Why are you so listless?

358
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,200
I'm not feeling well. I've got a cold.

359
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,000
- Have you taken any medicine?
- I have.

360
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,600
Enjoy yourselves. I'm going back to rest.

361
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:16,000
Go to bed early.

362
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,000
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

363
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,100
What's up with Xiao Huang?

364
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:28,600
She hasn't eaten much lately, and she's sick now.

365
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,200
Is there trouble in our village?

366
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,600
No, there isn't.

367
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:34,900
Would I be clueless about troubles in the village?

368
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,800
Then, that's good. That's good.

369
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,700
But A'Yao has been behaving oddly recently.

370
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:43,800
When I bump into him, he doesn't respond when I call out to him.

371
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,600
The matter with the bookstore is left hanging.

372
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:48,000
The homestay hasn't been resold as well.

373
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:50,200
Both of them are pretty stressed out.

374
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:54,400
Chairman Xie's mouth ulcers are really bad these days.

375
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,400
When people are stressed and in a bad mood,

376
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:58,200
they tend to have health problems.

377
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,000
Before the college entrance examinations,

378
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,800
my daughter suffered from a low fever for half a month.

379
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:04,000
We went to the hospital but couldn't detect any issues.

380
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,000
In the end, she recovered once the examinations were over.

381
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,400
Looks like she did well.

382
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,800
How do you feel? Better now?

383
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,700
I feel amazing. I feel so relaxed now.

384
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,700
All done. Thank you.

385
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:18,000
- Thank you, Xiao Bai.
- You're welcome.

386
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,700
- Xiao Yu, give me your hand.
- Okay.

387
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,100
What happened to your hand?

388
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:24,200
It's an issue from playing the guitar. Tenosynovitis.

389
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,400
Be gentle.

390
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,700
I'm not using much strength.

391
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:30,100
Okay. Have fun. I'm leaving.

392
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:31,600
- Goodbye, Aunty A'Gui.
- Bye, Aunty.

393
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,600
- Thank you, Xiao Bai.
- You're welcome.

394
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,500
Goodbye.

395
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,800
Be gentle, Sister.

396
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:37,400
I'm not using any strength.

397
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:40,300
Relax! Relax.

398
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:42,400
What a big baby.

399
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,400
- Relax.
- Relax.

400
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,900
- It doesn't hurt, does it?
- Nah, it doesn't.

401
