♫ <i>It's just another day</i> ♫

418
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:50,200
My friend sent over plums from Yunnan, but they're a little sour. Try one.

419
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,900
Thank you, Second Sister.

420
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,700
Second Sister,

421
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,400
is this the one?

422
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,000
Is he handsome?

423
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:02,100
Yes, he is.

424
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,200
It's just a pity.

425
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,000
Why?

426
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,200
It's a pity you met while you were on vacation.

427
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:11,400
You aren't in the same place.

428
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,200
After watching this promotional video,

429
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,400
do you feel like visiting that place?

430
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,600
Yes.

431
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,100
I think it's pretty good.

432
00:27:23,100 --> 00:27:25,000
What appealed to you?

433
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:29,524
The environment and the atmosphere of the people there seem relaxing.

434
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,400
I think so, too.

435
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:35,500
It's a very quaint place.

436
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:39,500
It has natural greenery, lakes, and mountains.

437
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:42,200
Time passes very slowly there.

438
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:48,500
It's reminiscent of our time as kids at Grandma's place.

439
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,400
There were so many white clouds.

440
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:55,800
It also has... fresh air,

441
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,800
radiant sunlight,

442
00:27:57,800 --> 00:28:00,600
and exceptional weather.

443
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:06,800
It's completely different from life here.

444
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:09,800
In that small place, the same few people

445
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,700
live with each other.

446
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,900
You will see others,

447
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,600
as well as yourself.

448
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:22,800
You can even feel the essence of life.

449
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:27,900
It's not about living in a big mansion or driving a luxury car.

450
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:34,900
It's about chatting with friends in the sun after a meal.

451
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:49,000
We work so hard just to be able to

452
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:52,000
enjoy life outside of work.

453
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,800
How wonderful.

454
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:59,300
In my current situation, I don't know when I can take a vacation.

455
00:29:00,100 --> 00:29:03,900
Before I got married, I went on trips with my friends every year.

456
00:29:03,900 --> 00:29:06,500
At that time, Sister Nan Nan was able to

457
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:09,400
offer us staff family discounts.

458
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,000
In a blink of an eye,

459
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,800
I'm a mother now.

460
00:29:14,900 --> 00:29:17,600
It's been a year since Sister Nan Nan passed away.

461
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:20,500
Time flies. It's like a dream.

462
00:29:22,100 --> 00:29:25,600
It's like flipping through a book, page after page.

463
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:27,600
Page after page.

464
00:29:30,110 --> 00:29:31,110
<i>Coming.</i>

465
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,100
<i>Who is it?</i>
- <i>Aunty, it's me.</i>

466
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:36,200
Yulin! Here's a pumpkin for you.

467
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:37,600
My mom sent it over from my hometown.

468
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,100
It's organic. Good stuff.

469
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,700
- Who is it?
- <i>You're so kind!</i>

470
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:43,400
Yesterday, when I was shopping in the supermarket,

471
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:45,200
I met a high school friend who lives in Building 8.

472
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,600
She sells insurance.

473
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:48,510
That's nice.

474
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:50,210
This naughty boy!

475
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:53,400
It's good for boys to be a little mischievous.

476
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,100
<i>Aunty, where's Hongdou?</i>

477
00:29:55,100 --> 00:29:57,300
<i>Her cousin is here. They're chatting in the room.</i>

478
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:59,600
I'll go over and say hi.

479
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:00,700
<i>I still have stuff to do at home.</i>

480
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:01,900
<i>Don't go back. I'm leaving.</i>

481
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:03,660
<i>Stay for a bit.</i>

482
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:06,800
- Chief.
- It's hot!

483
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:09,200
Your dough is fermented excellently.

484
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,400
Of course. Let me do it.

485
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,900
It's a pity that you aren't selling buns, you know?

486
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:15,820
Come on. Hongdou!

487
00:30:15,820 --> 00:30:18,480
- Hongdou!
- All right.

488
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:21,100
Come over. Look, freshly steamed buns.

489
00:30:21,100 --> 00:30:23,400
Take them to Li Yulin.

490
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:25,800
What's with that?

491
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:28,000
She gave us pumpkins and free-range eggs.

492
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,800
Besides, you should hang out with your classmates.

493
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:33,900
Don't just stare at your home at home.

494
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:35,800
Here's one more box.

495
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,600
Daughter, as the lobby manager of a hotel,

496
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:41,200
are you afraid of meeting people?

497
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:44,190
I'm the Deputy Manager of the Rooms Division.

498
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,400
Did you hear that? Deputy Manager of Rooms Division.

499
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,600
- Deputy Manager.
- I'm her dad.

500
00:31:01,700 --> 00:31:03,800
You took so long to come back.

501
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,400
Their house is so noisy.

502
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:09,600
I went to the roof with her for a breather.

503
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:12,300
She tried to sell insurance to you again, right?

504
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:16,100
It's not easy to balance a part-time job with raising a child.

505
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:17,600
Don't buy any if you don't want to.

506
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,100
It's fine.

507
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:24,300
It's so snobbish to sell things when old classmates meet.

508
00:31:24,300 --> 00:31:25,800
Don't say that.

509
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,700
Interpersonal relationships are the crux in such a small place.

510
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:33,400
Besides, insurance is usually sold to acquaintances first.

511
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,200
Isn't that just taking advantage of one's friends?

512
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,800
